<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FD92FC89FD69FCA4" box="[639,750,863,885]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Figs 42-49</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF5FFC50FC4BFC16" blockId="10.[178,1086,902,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
T y p e m a t e r i a l: 
<typeStatus id="54CC8830EF57A429FE46FC50FE78FC4B" box="[427,511,902,922]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Holotype</typeStatus>
: &quot; 
<collectingCountry id="F3607602EF57A429FDDFFC50FDEAFC4B" box="[562,621,902,922]" name="Nepal" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Nepal</collectingCountry>
: 361, Taplejung Dist. upper Simbua Khola, near Tseram, 10.-15.V.88, 3250- 
<quantity id="4C8F9B77EF57A429FE5FFC4BFE7CFC60" box="[434,507,925,945]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" unit="m" value="3350.0">3350 m</quantity>
, leg. Schawaller / 
<typeStatus id="54CC8830EF57A429FD47FC4BFC8EFC60" box="[682,777,925,945]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Holotypus</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName id="4C774D11EF57A429FCC4FC4BFC65FC60" authority="Assing, 2011" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[809,994,925,945]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schawalleri" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B903EA80EF57A429FCC4FC4BFC65FC60" box="[809,994,925,945]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Leptusa schawalleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23057FBEF57A429FC04FC4BFB92FC60" box="[1001,1045,925,945]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
det. V. Assing 2010&quot; (SMNS). 
<typeStatus id="54CC8830EF57A429FE45FC65FD83FC16" box="[424,516,947,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Paratypes</typeStatus>
: 1, 4: same data as 
<typeStatus id="54CC8830EF57A429FD01FC65FCBCFC16" box="[748,827,947,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">holotype</typeStatus>
(SMNS, cAss).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36D6519EF57A428FF5FFC00FC91FEDC" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="264" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF5FFC00FE81FBD8" blockId="10.[178,1085,982,1033]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
D e s c r i p t i o n: External characters (
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FD93FC00FD71FC3D" box="[638,758,982,1004]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Figs 42-43</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D11EF57A429FCBEFC00FC45FC3D" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[851,962,982,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiarens">
<emphasis id="B903EA80EF57A429FCBEFC00FC45FC3D" box="[851,962,982,1004]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">L. hiarens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF5FFBCEFEE6FB9A" blockId="10.[178,1085,1048,1099]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
Elytral suture not gaping posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FDD0FBCEFD0AFBFF" box="[573,653,1048,1070]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly convex (
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FEE4FBE3FED2FB9A" box="[265,341,1077,1099]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF2AFB8DFD96FB7A" blockId="10.[178,1085,1115,1195]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
: sternite VII unmodified; posterior margin of sternite VIII very weakly produced in the middle (
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FEDCFBAEFE06FB5F" box="[305,385,1144,1166]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); aedeagus ca. 
<quantity id="4C8F9B77EF57A429FDCFFBAEFDF8FB5F" box="[546,639,1144,1166]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long, shaped as in 
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FCBCFBAEFC18FB5F" box="[849,927,1144,1166]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
; apical lobe of paramere short and stout (
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FE54FB43FD81FB7A" box="[441,518,1173,1195]" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF2AFB6DFF5CFADA" blockId="10.[178,1086,1210,1291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
: sternite VIII of similar shape as in male, slightly less produced than in male; spermathecal capsule with distal portion of oval shape, without apical cuticular intrusion (
<figureCitation id="134C2A17EF57A429FBF9FB0EFF48FADA" captionStart="Figs 42-52" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1511,1531]" captionTargetBox="[189,1085,288,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[178,1085,287,1497]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 42-52: Leptusa schawalleri nov.sp. (42-49) and L. ilamensis PACE (50-52): (42) antenna; (43) median portion of pronotum; (44) sutural portion of elytra; (45, 50) male tergite VIII; (46, 51) male sternite VIII; (47, 52) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (48) apical lobe of paramere; (49) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324212/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF5FFACDFEC6FABA" blockId="10.[178,1085,1306,1387]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
E t y m o l o g y: The species is dedicated to Wolfgang Schawaller, specialist of 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D11EF57A429FF5FFAEEFEC0FA9F" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[178,327,1336,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tenebrionidae</taxonomicName>
, who collected the 
<typeStatus id="54CC8830EF57A429FDF1FAEEFDCFFA9C" box="[540,584,1336,1357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">type</typeStatus>
series of three of the species described in the present paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF57A429FF5FFAACFE9BF991" blockId="10.[178,1085,1402,1600]" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: This species is reliably distinguished from the syntopic 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D11EF57A429FF5FFA4EFE9CFA7C" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[178,283,1431,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiarens">
<emphasis id="B903EA80EF57A429FF5FFA4EFE9CFA7C" box="[178,283,1431,1453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">L. hiarens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only by the fully contiguous elytral suture (posteriorly gaping in 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D11EF57A429FC26FA4EFBB2FA7C" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[971,1077,1431,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiarens">
<emphasis id="B903EA80EF57A429FC26FA4EFBB2FA7C" box="[971,1077,1431,1453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="263">L. hiarens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by the sexual characters, particularly the completely different morphology of the median lobe of the aedeagus (which readily distinguishes it also from all other consubgeners), the stouter apical lobe of the paramere, as well as by the different morphology of the spermatheca (shape of the distal portion of the capsule, absence of an apical cuticular intrusion).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC83692EF56A428FF5FFF0DFC91FEDC" blockId="11.[178,1085,219,270]" pageId="11" pageNumber="264">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d n a t u r a l h i s t o r y: The 
<typeStatus id="54CC8830EF56A428FCB4FF0DFCFAFF21" box="[857,893,219,240]" pageId="11" pageNumber="264">type</typeStatus>
locality and the ecological circumstances are identical to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D11EF56A428FD44FF2FFC97FEDF" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[681,784,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiarens">
<emphasis id="B903EA80EF56A428FD44FF2FFC97FEDF" box="[681,784,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="264">L. hiarens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
